website_summaries.verdict: A classic bar cabinet with a large storage compartment. Strong and stable solid wood construction.
pros: Stands out for its spacious storage compartment with two adjustable shelves
The dark tobacco brown stain lacquer finish is easy to keep clean
Wine rack holds up to 12 bottles
cons: Some users report the pre-drilled guide holes for the door don't align correctly

customer_reviews.title: Great quality wine cabinet and it looks great
customer_reviews.text: Great quality wine cabinet and it looks great! I made one small adjustment by drilling holes for the bottom shelf 3/4in higher manually so that I could fit liquor bottles on the bottom shelf. Minus 1 star as I'm not sure if I spent more time building the cabinet or trying to remove the sticker on the inside of the cabinet that is impossible to remove in less than 1000 tiny paper pieces.
customer_reviews.author: Madeleine Bogdan

customer_reviews.title: Good material, sturdy but the door could be better ...
customer_reviews.text: Good material, sturdy but the door could be better -1 STAR BECAUSE some idiot thought it would be a good idea to put a thin paper sticker on the inside face of the cabinet. One of those suckers that just rip and get worse the harder you try. Theres a special place for you in hell my friend
customer_reviews.author: Suleyman Kahyaoglu

customer_reviews.title: Exactly what I needed
customer_reviews.text: Exactly what I was looking for, in the small space I wanted. Delivered well, box a little beat up, but the contents were undamaged all the way to Hawai‘i. Put together by myself in an hour and all I needed was a philips head screwdriver, everything else was supplied. Directions are very clear and parts well labelled and organized. I adjusted the shelves to accommodate service glassware, whiskey glasses, and whiskey bottles. I would definitely recommend this to a good friend.
customer_reviews.author: B. K. Rubio

customer_reviews.title: Decent cabinet
customer_reviews.text: This is a very nice, solid wood cabinet. Not made of MDF or pressboard with laminate like a lot of other furniture for sale. Has a very nice look and feel, but assembly was a little tricky. Uses cam locks to assemble, and if you thread the dowels in like you think you normally should, the cams won't grab properly. So, plan ahead. Once together, nice and solid, but the shelf spacing is too small for a regular liquor bottle. Great for glasses though.
customer_reviews.author: Joe

customer_reviews.title: Good furniture, poor production
customer_reviews.text: Nice piece of furniture, easy enough to assemble. Would have been 5 stars, except: Instructions vague at points and had typos, and there’s a big warning sticker in the main cabinet that does NOT peal off whole; wasted half hour scraping it off scuffing the inside.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: It's OK for our use but it is not a ...
customer_reviews.text: It's OK for our use but it is not a quality piece. It also had several "nicked" wood panels that were still wrapped up/ boxed up/ shipped to me. The door is set up to open from left to right; I reversed the hinges, turned the door upside down, and installed it to open in the other orientation.
customer_reviews.author: Fox

customer_reviews.title: My son put it together and it looks great and is very sturdy
customer_reviews.text: My son put it together and it looks great and is very sturdy. One thing, it does has a strong smell of wood stain or something chemical. Once you open the door, the strong smell hits you. I've had it for about three weeks now and it still smells strong, probably will have to leave the door open and let it air out.
customer_reviews.author: Sonia

customer_reviews.title: Solid and good looking
customer_reviews.text: I couldn’t believe how solid and sturdy this cabinet is. It’s a great value for the price and looks great.

customer_reviews.title: Beautiful
customer_reviews.text: Overall I have been very satisfied with this product. It looks nice and seems very sturdy. I actually ordered two and have placed one in each corner of my dining room. I use it to store wine glasses and stemware as well as some wine bottles. One of the units was very difficult to put together, some of the holes and pegs were difficult to line up, but once my husband finally got it assembled, it looked great. I do plan to change the handle to something more decorative.
customer_reviews.author: DJA

customer_reviews.title: A Nice Piece Ruined By Unnecessary Stickers!!
customer_reviews.text: This is better quality than expected for the price. A bit smaller than displayed but would have been a great piece of furniture if it were not for the low quality and impossible to remove stickers. Even careful removal damaged the surface. Assembly is as expected.

customer_reviews.title: Very good quality
customer_reviews.text: Very good quality product. Solid wood not pressed. Excellent finish. Instruction manual not very good and instructions are lacking clarity. Manufacturer put some labels inside one panel of the cabinet and it was very hard to remove and it leaves some glue on the finish of the wood. Same thing for 2 labels on the tempered glass of the front door. It took forever to remove the glue. I would buy this item again minus the instructions and the labels.
customer_reviews.author: Laurence

customer_reviews.title: Real Wood!

customer_reviews.title: Color isn't true to photo
customer_reviews.text: Overall I'm not completely happy with this purchase. The color of this wine rack is more of a coffee brown than the cherry-ish tones pictured. Wasn't too challenging to put together but one side isn't completely flush (cam locks won't lock and the dowels are showing). The wine bottle section also wobbles a bit since the screws just stop screwing after a point. For the price I was expecting at least the color pictured and described but I'll just deal with it since it's already put together.
customer_reviews.author: Kayla

customer_reviews.title: Difficult to build!
customer_reviews.text: I'll start by saying that the cabinet is a nice looking addition to my dining room. Now, the bad part: horribly, horribly difficult to construct. The most complex piece of build-it-yourself furniture I've ever put together....from hardware that I'd never seen used before to awkward instructions, this piece is pretty hard to make...Oh, and quality control is a real problem...I've other posts about poorly drilled holes, but the didn't fully drill several of mine all of the way through. All in all, a three hour job that could've been done in an hour and a half if designed better.
customer_reviews.author: F

Overall it looks nice and functions pretty good. We ended up not using one of the shelves b/c taller liquor bottle wouldn't have fit inside. Also, the shelves aren't very deep so you can't fit a ton of glasses.
